{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HsHCFCmxYsKdKTo4D9USq5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting. crdb-cluster-2 says it's \"unable to contact the other nodes\". But crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are running. Let me check their logs and status.\n\nThe issue is that the StatefulSet is doing a rolling update, and since crdb-cluster-2 was the first to be updated (rolling updates go from the highest ordinal to the lowest by default), it was restarted first. But crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 might still be running in insecure mode, so they can't communicate with crdb-cluster-2 which is now in secure mode.\nSo the rolling update is stuck because crdb-cluster-2 can't join the cluster in secure mode while the others are still insecure. This is the core problem with switching from insecure to secure mode - all nodes need to transition simultaneously rather than one at a time.\n\nI'm considering a few approaches: I could delete all the pods at once to force them to restart with the new configuration together, use the partition strategy differently, or manually restart them all in parallel. Let me check the current pod ages to understand the timing better.\n\nLooking at the ages, pods 0 and 1 haven't been restarted yet since they're older than pod 2, which means the rolling update is stuck—pod 2 came up in secure mode but can't become ready because the other pods are still in insecure mode and won't communicate with it. The cleanest solution is to delete all the CRDB pods simultaneously so they all restart with the new TLS configuration at the same time.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":763,"cache_read_input_tokens":37944,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":763},"output_tokens":46,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diag